        "collapsible_tab_zEHWUh": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are Arms of Andes products covered by a warranty?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Yes, manufacturing defects in Arms of Andes clothing are eligible for a full refund. Please note that natural wear and tear, including pilling and abrasion, are not considered factory defects and are therefore not covered by the Warranty. Further, damage incurred by the user – including, but not limited to, rips, tears and damage occurring during washing when care instructions are not followed – are not covered by the Warranty. In the unlikely event that you receive an Arms of Andes garment that you feel is defective, please contact our customer service department so that we can arrange the return and inspection of the garment to determine if the defect falls under the Warranty.</p>",
            "page": "",
